This paper deals with the denotational semantics of first-order logic and its adaptation to include search and choice. This makes it relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Programming Languages (cs.PL), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), and Software Engineering (cs.SE). However, since the paper focuses on the semantics of logic and constraint programming, cs.LO and cs.AI are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses conditions for sound search, which is relevant to cs.PL and cs.SE. Finally, the paper mentions future research on efficiency of search, which is relevant to cs.DS.
